HEADWORD: Pyrogenic
<hw>Pyr`o*gen"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Pyro-</ets>
+ <ets>-gen</ets> + <ets>-ic</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>Producing heat; -- said of substances, as septic poisons, which
elevate the temperature of the body and cause fever.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pyrogenous</ent>⟦br⟧
